Day 05 – Internship Log

Session Attended
Attended a session on RCM (Revenue Cycle Management), ETL process, and Docker.

Topics Covered
* Introduction to RCM and how hospitals and insurance systems work
* Understanding how claims are processed and tracked
* Basics of ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) process
* Introduction to cloud storage (GCP buckets)
* Overview of MongoDB and data storage
* Introduction to Docker and its purpose

Key Learnings
     RCM (Revenue Cycle Management)
* Hospitals send claims to insurance companies
* Payments are tracked and managed through the system
* Rejected or pending claims are followed up
* Each claim is tracked using versions

     ETL Process
* Extract data from CSV files or other sources
* Transform data by cleaning and applying logic
* Load processed data into database
* Remove invalid records and standardize data

     Data Storage
* Data is stored in databases like MongoDB
* Large data is handled using structured and unstructured formats

     Docker
* Docker is used to package the entire project with dependencies
* Helps run the project in any system without setup issues
* Docker image contains code, libraries, and environment
* Used to deploy pipeline in cloud

Learning Outcome
* Understood how real-time projects handle large data
* Learned basic workflow of ETL pipeline
* Gained idea about Docker usage in projects
* Understood how data moves from source to database

